1
00:00:00,541 --> 00:00:02,958
This tunnel, of course, they recognized each other

2
00:00:03,083 --> 00:00:05,875
Ahmad al-Hassan al-Ibrahim
and Abdullah al-Hassan al-Salama

3
00:00:06,541 --> 00:00:11,083
Ahmad al-Hassan knew that Abdullah
was imprisoned, but Abdullah did not know

4
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:14,708
They saw each other in the prison and checked on each other

5
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:17,708
Because they were Muslims, according to ISIS’s standards

6
00:00:18,416 --> 00:00:21,750
They were taken down into the
basement, and that made them feel relieved

7
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:26,916
They felt they would not be killed, God
willing, but were sad for those they left behind

8
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:33,041
They were considered part of the disbelievers’ section,
among them was a young man named Alaa from rural Aleppo

9
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:38,625
Of course, this basement, we knew there was
something abnormal happening in the prison

10
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:42,166
But we did not know what it was until the prisoners came out

11
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,291
Those who had entered that basement told us its story

12
00:00:45,166 --> 00:00:49,625
And this tunnel, of course, extended to the third neighborhood

13
00:00:50,125 --> 00:00:53,875
They had built it for escaping in case fighting broke out

14
00:00:56,083 --> 00:00:59,875
So they could go in and out freely, but they rarely used it

15
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,750
They would open the door only occasionally

16
00:01:02,291 --> 00:01:03,750
But we did not know what was inside

17
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:06,541
Even if there were prisoners inside, we did not know them

18
00:01:07,208 --> 00:01:10,541
We did not know about this matter,
because every day or every two days or more

19
00:01:10,708 --> 00:01:15,958
The door would open and close, but we never knew what was behind it

20
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:20,791
Interviewer: From what you said, how did you know the door was opened?

21
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:25,625
This door, of course, had some modifications and wall divisions made

22
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:30,291
Some walls were removed and others built during the last period

23
00:01:30,708 --> 00:01:34,041
But when the door opened, we could see it through the window

24
00:01:34,125 --> 00:01:38,875
We knew there was a door opposite
the entrance door and the garage door

25
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,875
There was a door that, when opened, we could hear its sound clearly

26
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:44,583
And right afterward, the humidity would rise

27
00:01:44,958 --> 00:01:48,625
And in summer, the air became unusually cold

28
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:52,833
We knew something was there, but we did not know what it was
